---sql theory
---1answer
in sql char is only applicable for charecters but varchar is applicable for numbers,charecters,specisl symbols etc....
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

---2nd answer
in sql the where clause is used before the order by and the having clause is used after the order by.
where alause is used to filter the rows
having is used to filter the groups
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
---3rd answer
the purpose of group by clause in sql it groups the values of different departments into one group
it is mainly used with aggeregate function like it groups the values after we get the results of aggregate functions.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
---4th answer
1.data definition language DDL
it is an sql command
in this commands are
create,alter,drop,truncate
---------------------------------------------
2.data manipulation languade DML
insert,delete,update
---------------------------------------------
3.data control language DCL
grant, revoke
---------------------------------------------
4.transaction control language TCL
commit,rollback
---------------------------------------------
---5th answer
create it creates a database  or table
alter it adds new column to existing table
drop it drops the structure of a table permanently...
